sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant UI as React Frontend
    participant BFF as UI BFF<br/>8080/TCP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MR as Model Registry<br/>REST Proxy<br/>8080/TCP
    participant DB as MySQL/PostgreSQL<br/>3306/5432/TCP
    participant Controller as MR Controller<br/>8081/TCP
    participant CSI as Storage Initializer<br/>(Init Container)
    participant KServe as KServe<br/>InferenceService
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Catalog as Model Catalog<br/>8080/TCP
    participant CatalogDB as PostgreSQL<br/>(Catalog)<br/>5432/TCP
    participant HF as Hugging Face<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AsyncJob as Async Upload Job
    participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Sigstore as Sigstore<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User, DB: Flow 1: Model Registration via REST API

    User->>UI: Browse/register models
    UI->>BFF: GET/POST /api/v1/model_registry/:id/*<br/>Bearer Token / kubeflow-userid
    BFF->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>ServiceAccount + User token
    K8sAPI-->>BFF: Access granted
    BFF->>MR: GET/POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/*<br/>Token forwarding, ISTIO_MUTUAL
    MR->>DB: SQL query (GORM)<br/>Username/password, Optional TLS 1.2+
    DB-->>MR: Query result
    MR-->>BFF: JSON response
    BFF-->>UI: JSON response
    UI-->>User: Display results

    Note over Controller, DB: Flow 2: KServe InferenceService Sync

    KServe->>K8sAPI: Create/Update InferenceService CR
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch InferenceService CRs<br/>ServiceAccount token, TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: InferenceService event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: List Services (label: component=model-registry)<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Service endpoints
    Controller->>MR: Create/Update InferenceService resource<br/>Bearer token (K8s SA)
    MR->>DB: Upsert record
    DB-->>MR: Confirm
    MR-->>Controller: Success

    Note over CSI, S3: Flow 3: Model Serving via CSI Storage Initializer

    KServe->>CSI: Init container starts<br/>model-registry:// URI
    CSI->>MR: Resolve model URI<br/>GET /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/model_artifacts/*
    MR->>DB: Lookup artifact metadata
    DB-->>MR: Artifact location (S3/GCS/PVC)
    MR-->>CSI: Artifact metadata + storage URI
    CSI->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>Per-provider credentials
    S3-->>CSI: Model files
    CSI-->>KServe: Model ready in local path

    Note over AsyncJob, Sigstore: Flow 4: Async Model Upload Job

    User->>BFF: POST /api/v1/model_registry/:id/model_transfer_jobs<br/>Upload intent + metadata
    BFF->>K8sAPI: Create K8s Job<br/>SAR check
    K8sAPI-->>BFF: Job created
    AsyncJob->>S3: Download from source<br/>AWS credentials, TLS 1.2+
    AsyncJob->>OCI: Push to destination registry<br/>Docker config credentials, TLS 1.2+
    AsyncJob->>Sigstore: Sign model (Fulcio/Rekor)<br/>Identity token, TLS 1.2+
    Sigstore-->>AsyncJob: Signature verified
    AsyncJob->>MR: Register model/version/artifact<br/>In-cluster, TLS 1.2+
    MR->>DB: Insert records
    DB-->>MR: Confirm
    MR-->>AsyncJob: Registration complete

    Note over Catalog, HF: Flow 5: Model Catalog Discovery

    User->>UI: Browse model catalog
    UI->>BFF: GET /api/v1/model_catalog/models
    BFF->>Catalog: GET /api/model_catalog/v1alpha1/models<br/>Token forwarding
    Catalog->>CatalogDB: Query models (GORM)<br/>Username/password
    CatalogDB-->>Catalog: Model list
    Catalog-->>BFF: Catalog results
    BFF-->>UI: JSON response

    Note right of Catalog: Background: Catalog syncs from sources
    Catalog->>HF: Fetch model metadata<br/>API key (optional), TLS 1.2+
    HF-->>Catalog: Model metadata
    Catalog->>CatalogDB: Upsert catalog entries
